texts.text: Many historical versions in the Minecraft launcher are labeled as "old_alpha", despite not all actually being from the Alpha development phase[1] (though this may be due to a more general use of the software development term "alpha"). This term may refer to:

Pre-classic, the first private development phase of Minecraft.[2]
Classic, originally named "Minecraft Alpha".
Indev, where Minecraft was now "in development".
Infdev, infinite world generation development.
Alpha, the development phase of Minecraft preceding Beta.
"TigIRC logs" (archived) – Archive.org, May 16, 2009, UTC–4. "(12:07:06) notch: minecraft alpha is available. I need someone on windows, someone on mac and someone on linux!"
